cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper focuses on active topology discovery within the IPv6 Internet, which is a subfield of network infrastructure and protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the efficiency and efficacy of various IPv6 hitlists and target generation methods, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper employs randomized probing techniques and analyzes the results, which could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper shares its prober implementation and discovered IPv6 topology results, which could be considered as a contribution to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
